Turn on the light. Stand up. Get your dressing gown and put it on. Open the pocket and take the tablet of buffered analgesic (i.e., aspirin). Take the screwdriver and toothbrush. Go south onto your Front Porch and get the junk mail. Go south again to Front of House and take bleary-eyed notice of the bulldozer.

>turn on light
>stand up
>take dressing gown
>put on dressing gown
>open pockets
>take buffered analgesic
>take screwdriver
>take toothbrush
>go south
>take mail
>go south

Lie down in the mud to stop the bulldozer's progress. Wait three turns while the bulldozer approaches and finally stops. When Ford Prefect shows up, don't take his offered towel. Say Ford, what about my home. Wait two more turns while they are "deeply engrossed in conversation" and Ford persuades Prosser to switch places with you in the mud.

>lie down
>wait
>wait
>wait
>ask ford
>what about my home
>wait
>wait

After you stand up, head south and then west down the lane to the Pub. Wait. When Ford buys beer, drink the beer three times, and buy a cheese sandwich. If you haven't already, soon you will hear your house being knocked down. Go east out of the pub, give the sandwich to the dog, then go north to what's left of your house. If you like, spend a couple of turns taking it out on Prosser (yell at him, hit him, etc.). Soon a Vogon Constructor Fleet will arrive to do to Earth what Prosser just did to your house.

>go south
>go west
>wait
>drink beer
>drink beer
>drink beer
>buy cheese sandwich
>go east
>give sandwich to dog
>go north

Wait twice. Pick up the "small black device" that Ford drops. Examine it - it's an Electronic Thumb, which lets you try to flag down a ride on any passing spaceships. Press the green button to hitch a ride aboard one of the conveniently located Vogon ships.

>wait
>wait
>pick up device
>examine device
>press green button

Wait four turns. Look closely at the room descriptions. Have you noticed a sense is now missing from the list of things you can't perceive? Smell the dark, and notice that something is "being waved" under your nose. Examine the shadow. Eat the peanuts that Ford gives you.

>wait
>wait
>wait
>wait
>smell dark
>examine shadow
>eat peanuts

The next order of business is to get a Babel fish into your ear. (Yeah, you heard me.) Examine the dispensing machine. Remove your gown and hang it on the hook. Wait one turn for Ford to fall asleep. Take the towel and satchel. Put the towel over the grate in the floor. Put the satchel in front of the dispenser's "robot panel". Put the junk mail on the satchel. Press the dispenser button. (Insert Rube Goldberg sequence here.) Squish!

>examine dispensing machine
>remove gown
>hang gown on hook
>wait
>take towel
>take satchel
>put towel over grate
>put satchel in front of panel
>put mail on satchel
>press dispenser button

Examine the case that holds the atomic vector plotter. Flip the switch, and make a note of the word and verse of the password to open the case. Wait four turns until some Vogon guards come to drag you to the poetry reading. Wait four more turns. Once the Captain begins ("Oh freddled gruntbuggly..."), enjoy the poetry. Wait. Pay close attention to get the password for the vector plotter case. Wait until you are returned to the Vogon Hold.

